Several works have rigorously investigated the FDI attack
by proposing various detectors or analyzing the damage
effects on the power system. For examples, Kosut et al. [26]
proposed a detection scheme based on generalized likelihood
ratio test while comparing with other two detectors based on
the residual error r derived from the state estimation that uses
minimum mean square error technique. The authors studied
the outcomes of maximizing the residual error and minimizing
the detection rate for the attack. Yuan et al. [32] identied
the attack launched in two different time periods (i.e.,
immediate and delayed attack) in which the former may lead
