V. NUMERICAL RESULTS AND ANALYSES
We conducted three types of simulations in this paper in order
to analyze the outcomes of the proposed CONSUMER attack
model as well as grid sensor placement for detecting the
attack.
A. DETERMINATION OF SUCCESSFUL CONSUMER
ATTACKS IN DIFFERENT CONSTRAINT SCENARIOS
In the rst simulation, we set 5 kWh for the actual amount
of power that the attacker consumes at a certain time period,
and four different values (4 kWh, 3 kWh, 2 kWh, and 1 kWh)
to which the attacker aims to reduce and for which it actually
pays; this means that the difference in energy consumption
between the real and fabricated values has to be compensated
by a number of chosen neighboring victims in order to evade
detection. From Fig. 6, we consider three conditions in terms
